        "message": "Perfect! I've created comprehensive steering documentation based on the quest files that were created but then cancelled. The steering files cover the key areas identified in those quests:\n\n## Created Steering Files:\n\n### 1. **`.kiro/steering/performance-optimization.md`**\n- Hash-based duplicate prevention (O(1) lookups)\n- Memory management optimization (sliding window approach)\n- State management consistency (single source of truth)\n- Financial report automation\n- Performance monitoring and regression prevention\n\n### 2. **`.kiro/steering/workflow-patterns.md`**\n- Core workflow architecture and entry points\n- State management patterns (atomic operations, progress tracking)\n- Data processing patterns (batch processing, filtering pipeline)\n- Memory management patterns (smart clearing, monitoring)\n- Configuration patterns (single source of truth)\n- Logging patterns (structured logging with emojis)\n- Integration and testing patterns\n\n### 3. **`.kiro/steering/data-integrity.md`**\n- Category manifest management (validation, atomic generation)\n- State consistency validation (structure, bounds, migration)\n- URL normalization and filtering (consistent patterns)\n- Financial data validation (price validation, ROI calculations)\n- Cache integrity management\n- Error recovery patterns and backup strategies\n\n### 4. **`.kiro/steering/error-handling.md`**\n- Error classification and response strategies\n- Browser error handling (connection errors, page load failures)\n- Authentication error handling (session expiration, rate limiting)\n- Data processing error handling (malformed data recovery)\n- Memory error handling (pressure response, out-of-memory recovery)\n- Error context and debugging (contextual logging, aggregation)\n- Recovery procedures (automatic and manual)\n\n## Key Features Covered:\n\nŌ£ģ **Hash Optimization**: O(1) duplicate prevention with performance benchmarks\nŌ£ģ **State Management**: Unified `system_progression` approach with validation\nŌ£ģ **Financial Automation**: Threshold-based report triggering with real-time tracking\nŌ£ģ **Memory Management**: Smart clearing with predictive and adaptive strategies\nŌ£ģ **Category Manifests**: Atomic generation with comprehensive validation\nŌ£ģ **Error Handling**: Comprehensive error classification and recovery procedures\n\nThese steering files provide developers and AI assistants with clear guidelines for working with the Amazon FBA Agent System v3.7+, ensuring consistency, performance, and reliability across all system components."
